article.description: Brittney Martin had 24 points on 12-of-16 shooting with seven rebounds, four assists and three steals to help No. 22 Oklahoma State beat Kansas 71-49 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: No. 22 Oklahoma State women beat Kansas 71-49
article.linkText: No. 22 Oklahoma State women beat Kansas 71-49
article.story:
STILLWATER, Okla. --  Brittney Martin had 24 points on 12-of-16 shooting with seven rebounds, four assists and three steals to help No. 22 Oklahoma State beat Kansas 71-49 on Wednesday night.

The Cowgirls (20-7, 10-6 Big 12) led the entire way, building a 33-13 lead 3:20 before halftime and holding their advantage between 18 and 24 in the second half.

Martin had 14 of her points in the first half and Oklahoma State led 37-18 going into the break. The Cowgirls were 31 of 57 (54.4 percent) from the floor while holding Kansas to 19 of 52 (36.5 percent).

Kaylee Jensen added 18 points and 12 rebounds and Sydney Walton was 3 of 5 from 3-point range with 11 points.

Lauren Aldridge had 13 points and Tyler Johnson scored 11 for the Jayhawks (5-22, 0-16), who have lost 18 straight.
